  "local_port": 50700,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Bank Accounts: How do I know whether my bank account is linked to my Aadhaar card or not?",
  "response": "To check if your bank account is linked to your Aadhaar card, you can follow several methods:\n\n1. **SMS Notification:**\n   - If your bank account was recently linked to your Aadhaar card, you might have received an SMS notification from your bank confirming the linkage.\n\n2. **Internet Banking:**\n   - Log in to your bank's internet banking portal.\n   - Look for an option related to 'Aadhaar Linking' or 'Aadhaar/UID Status' in the user profile section.\n   - It will show you the status of your Aadhaar linkage.\n\n3. **Mobile Banking App:**\n   - Open your bank's official mobile banking app.\n   - Navigate to the profile or settings section.\n   - You should find an option to check 'Aadhaar Linking Status.'\n\n4. **Aadhaar Website:**\n   - Visit the official UIDAI website (uidai.gov.in).\n   - Click on 'Check Aadhaar & Bank Account Linking Status.'\n   - Enter your 12-digit Aadhaar number and the security code.\n   - You will receive an OTP on your registered mobile number. Enter the OTP to view the linking status.\n\n5. **Contact Your Bank:**\n   - Call your bank's customer service or visit the nearest branch.\n   - Provide your Aadhaar number and account details to the bank representative, and they can confirm the linking status for you.\n\n6. **Passbook/Account Statement:**\n   - Sometimes, the account statement or passbook mentions the Aadhaar linkage status once it is linked.\n\n7. **ATM:**\n   - Some banks provide the option to check Aadhaar linking status through their ATMs.\n\nIf you find that your Aadhaar is not linked to your bank account, you can follow the steps provided by your bank to complete the linkage process.",
